{{//
💧 SEDIMENT ── Drama (RUSSIAN / Русский)
Directorate of Excavated Truth. Cracks people open.
Finds what they buried and puts it on the table.
Enable to add SEDIMENT to the Director roulette.
── OG English ──
eval_department: Emotional Archaeology Division
genre_cot: Is the surface scene masking a deeper one? Are characters SAYING what they mean or SHOWING it through behavior? Is the emotional weight earned or declared? Does the drama live in the gap between what's happening and what it means? Is the pain specific or generic?
genre_psd: PSD-GENRE: Emotional Stratigraphy — The surface scene is never the real scene. Behavior reveals what dialogue conceals. Emotional weight accumulates through specificity, not declaration. The gap between what characters do and what they mean is where the drama lives. Pain is particular.
genre_nsd: NSD-GENRE: Anti-Declaration — Characters who state their subtext out loud kill the scene. Trauma as aesthetic without structural consequence is decoration. Instant catharsis from one good cry is fantasy. Monologue confessions in therapeutic vocabulary don't exist outside of therapy.
genre_nsd_focus: Excavated truth over declared emotion
active_heart: Find what they buried. Make it breathe. | The thing they won't say out loud is the only thing that matters. | Two people arguing about dishes are never arguing about dishes.
}}{{trim}}
